title: Scourge of the West
description: Hail the conquering zero! Clueless "war hero" Captain Wilton Parmenter takes command of Fort Courage.

title: Don't Look Now, One of Our Cannon Is Missing
description: In order to get the Hakawi to make more blankets O'Rourke agrees to let them borrow the fort's cannon for their Moon Festival. Agarn is against this but he eventually goes along with it. O'Rourke has all the bases covered for this deception including keeping Parmenter busy on a date with Wrangler Jane...but he doesn't count on a surprise visit by General Grant.

title: The Phantom Major
description: It's pay call at Fort Courage when a top secret letter from Washington arrives. F Troop has been chosen as a test troop for a new style of Indian fighting...infiltration through camouflage. Major Bentley-Royce of the Bengal Lancers will be instructing them. He is a master of disguise and a living legend known as 'The Phantom Major'. He also wants to prove the fort is obsolete. O'Rourke and Agarn will have to enlist the Hakawi in order to prove him wrong.

title: Corporal Agarn's Farewell to the Troops
description: There's a $5,000 reward out for the capture of the Colton brothers and Parmenter decides to go after them. Meanwhile O'Rourke's horse and Agarn are both suffering from stomach pains. The prognosis is bad for the horse and Agarn overhears the doc and O'Rourke talking and thinks it's about him. Convinced he is dying Agarn writes a confessional letter to the Inspector General.

title: The Return of Bald Eagle
description: Renegade Indian Bald Eagle has been spotted by Fort Dodge and is believed to be heading towards Fort Courage. His reputation as wild and unpredictable precedes him and Parmenter prepares the Fort for an attack. He is crazy and attacks the fort singlehandedly. When the attack fails he is captured but he escapes and takes Parmenter with him. O'Rourke, Agarn and Jane head off in pursuit.

title: Dirge for the Scourge
description: Jane is disgusted with the saloon and the riff-raff it attracts and insists that Parmenter close it down. Parmenter looks into it and decides she's right and embarks on a plan to clean up the town. Meanwhile gunfighter Sam Urp is in town and after several clumsy accidental meetings with Parmenter swears he will gun him down next time he sees him. O'Rourke and Agarn can't afford to lose Parmenter so they set out to save him.

title: The Girl from Philadelphia
description: An old girlfriend of Captain Parmenter's visits Fort Courage to encourage him to return back east.

title: Old Ironpants
description: Captain Parmenter goes to command school and returns a tough Army officer that no one likes.

title: Me Heap Big Injun
description: Agarn joins the Hekawi tribe and turns out to be a better Indian than any other brave.

title: She's Only a Build in a Girdled Cage
description: When Dobbs' mother comes to visit she is mistaken for a dance hall singer.

title: A Gift from the Chief
description: After saving Wild Eagle's life, Captain Parmenter is given a baby.

title: Honest Injun
description: A conman comes to town taking the troopers money, which is O'Rourke's job.

title: O'Rourke vs. O'Reilly
description: A woman comes to town and takes over O'Rourke's saloon.

title: The 86 Proof Spring
description: Captain Parmenter is determined to find the Hekawi's whiskey supply that O'Rourke has stashed at the fort.

title: Here Comes the Tribe
description: The chief's daughter is kidnapped and F Troop swings into action.

title: Iron Horse Go Home
description: O'Rourke manipulates Capt. Parmenter into suggesting an incoming railroad be routed through Fort Courtage. That way, the bar that O'Rourke secretly owns will receive a windfall. To accomplish this, the U.S. Army must persuade the nearby Indians to move. They do so -- right into Fort Courage.

title: Our Hero, What's His Name?
description: Agarn gets a dear john letter from his girl Betty Lou and O'Rourke devises a scheme to keep them together. He proposes sending her a letter telling her of Agarn's bravery and the fact that single handedly he killed Geronimo. What they don't plan on is Betty Lou's father printing the letter in the newspaper and Agarn becoming a national hero. Geronimo has also read the newspaper and is intent on seeking revenge against Agarn. While all this transpires Parmenter is determined to capture a bear which has been seen near the fort.

title: Wrongo Starr and the Lady in Black
description: A natural jinx comes to F Troop and gets involved with a black widow who had four husbands.

title: El Diablo
description: While the men of F Troop are undergoing their annual physicals word comes that the Mexican bandit El Diablo is at large. It turns out that he and Corporal Agarn are cousins and look exactly alike. Agarn with the troop under his command set out to capture Diablo...but Diablo has taken Parmenter, Jane, O'Rourke and Dobbs prisoner.

title: Go for Broke
description: Jane's cousin helps O'Rourke replace the F Troop pension fund by entering a poker game.

title: The New I.G.
description: An Army major comes to Fort Courage who wants to wipe out the Hekawis.

title: Spy, Counterspy, Counter Counterspy
description: The War Department's testing of a new bulletproof vest at Fort Courage is hampered by two competing spies.

title: The Courtship of Wrangler Jane
description: To have the Captain move off post, O'Rourke plays cupid for him and Wrangler Jane.

title: Play, Gypsy, Play
description: A group of visiting Gypsies crown Agarn their long lost prince.

title: Reunion for O'Rourke
description: O'Rourke has been in the Army for twenty-five years.

title: Captain Parmenter, One Man Army
description: When F Troop finds out that none of them are legally enlisted, the troopers leave and only Captain Parmenter remains to fight off an Indian attack.

title: Don't Ever Speak to Me Again
description: Fort Courage is to receive a citation from the Secretary of War for having the best morale in the army. Unfortunately this is right on the eve of a wave of arguments that sweep the fort.

title: Too Many Cooks Spoil the Troop
description: After their cook is transferred, Agarn takes over so they can order excess supplies and sell them to the Indians.

title: Indian Fever
description: Agarn's sanity is questioned when he keeps seeing an Indian in the fort and no one else does.

title: Johnny Eagle Eye
description: O'Rourke and Agarn get Wild Eagle's nephew entered into the Army sharp shooting contest.

title: A Fort's Best Friend Is Not a Mother
description: When Captain Parmenter's mother arrives, she insists that he be transferred to a post back east.

title: Lieutenant O'Rourke, Front and Center
description: O'Rourke gets a promotion to lieutenant and is being transferred which could doom O'Rourke Enterprises.

title: The Day the Indians Won
description: The Hekawis - the tribe that invented the peace pipe - are ordered to go on the warpath so they attack Fort Courage.

title: Will the Real Captain Try to Stand Up
description: Captain Parmenter is temporarily replaced by the town drunk to impress his visiting daughter.

title: The Singing Mountie
description: Shades of Nelson Eddy as a singing Mountie shows up looking for Agarn's French Canadian cousin.

title: How to Be F Troop Without Really Trying
description: Everyone in F Troop is transferred except for Agarn who must train the new troops that are worse than his comrades.

title: Bye, Bye, Balloon
description: Fort Courage is visited by a Prussian balloonist.

title: Reach for the Sky, Pardner
description: Agarn and O'Rourke volunteer to guard the replacement payroll after the first one is stolen.

title: The Great Troop Robbery
description: A trickster tries to get Agarn blamed for his robberies.

title: The West Goes Ghost
description: Four F Troopers take over a ghost town hoping to get rich when the railroad finally comes through.

title: Yellow Bird
description: A white woman raised by Indians starts to take after the Captain.

title: The Ballot of Corporal Agarn
description: The two candidates for mayor of Passaic New Jersey, Agarn's hometown, come out West to get his vote since the election was tied and they need his absentee ballot to break the tie.

title: Did Your Father Come from Ireland?
description: While Sgt. O'Rourke is off on a horse buying mission, his father, Morgan O'Rourke, arrives from Ireland at Fort Courage and unintentionally raises havoc at the fort and even the Hakawi camp.

title: For Who the Bugle Tolls
description: A visiting Colonel judges a troop by its bugler and Fort Courage has the world's worse.

title: Miss Parmenter
description: Wilton's sister has eyes for the company bugler.

title: La Dolce Courage
description: An Italian father and daughter visit Fort Courage pursued by a spurned lover.

title: Wilton, the Kid
description: Kid Vicious, a dead ringer for Captain Parmenter, comes to town.

title: The Return of Wrongo Starr
description: Natural jinx Wrongo Starr returns driving a load of dynamite.

title: Survival of the Fittest
description: Parmenter and Agarn go on a survival test where O'Rourke makes sure that they can find food.

title: Bring on the Dancing Girls
description: Agarn and O'Rourke go after the man that swindled them out of their saloon.

title: The Loco Brothers
description: Two renegade Indians captured Captain Parmenter, but are just looking for company.

title: From Karate with Love
description: East meets West in this episode when the men of Fort Courage offer sanctuary for a young Japanese woman who is fleeing an arranged marriage with a man she does not love. This is good for O'Rourke and Agarn who want the tribe to start manufacturing Kimonos, parasols, and fans but don't plan on a Samurai warrior who is determined to bring her back to Japan where she will fulfill her destiny and marry.

title: The Sergeant and the Kid
description: A ten year old boy shows up at Fort Courage and wants to join up.

title: What Are You Doing After the Massacre?
description: A 147 year old Hekawi chief wants the land that Fort Courage sits on and lays siege to the fort.

title: A Horse of Another Color
description: The wild horse that the Captain wants to capture for Jane, O'Rourke wants to sell to the circus.

title: V Is for Vampire
description: Count Sforza, an emigrant from Transylvania, arrives in town. He comes in a hearse, has pale skin and has a crow he calls "Brother." The men of F-Troop suspect he may be a vampire, given the count's tendency to say, "Good evening," regardless of the time of day. When Jane can't be found, O'Rourke, Agarn and the Captain decide to check out Sforza's spooky mansion.

title: That's Show Biz
description: Agarn leaves the Army to manage a rock band called the Bedbugs.

title: The Day They Shot Agarn
description: Agarn faces the firing squad after the prisoner in his care escapes and kills Sergeant O'Rourke.

title: Only One Russian Is Coming! Only One Russian Is Coming!
description: Agarn's Russian cossack cousin falls for Wrangler Jane.

title: Guns, Guns, Who's Got the Guns?
description: The Captain goes on a spy mission to find out who's selling guns to the Indians.

title: Marriage, Fort Courage Style
description: A marriage broker comes to town scaring both Corporal Agarn and Captain Parmenter.

title: Carpetbagging, Anyone?
description: A man comes to town, buys the land that Fort Courage is on and then plans to throw out F Troop.

title: The Majority of Wilton
description: Wilton is eligible for promotion to Major, but first he must pass a rigorous examination. His attempts at study are jeopardized by a bad cold and various home remedies.

title: Our Brave in F Troop
description: Chief Wild Eagle is hiding at Fort Courage to visit the Army dentist; however a visiting general is impressed by this "soldier" and keeps promoting him.

title: Is This Fort Really Necessary?
description: An officer known for closing down forts comes to Fort Courage to get married.
